{"serial": "12017", "department_serial": 11, "code": "EL3084", "class": "*", "name": {"en": "Topics in Film Studies", "ch": "電影研究專題"}, "notice": {"en": "", "ch": ""}, "instructor": {"en": [], "ch": []}, "credits": 3, "time_loc": [{"time": {"week": 2, "session": ["6", "7", "8"]}, "loc": {"building": "C2", "room": "114"}}], "isRequired": false, "isFullSem": false, "MaxStu": 50, "department": {"ch": "英美語文學系", "en": "Department of English"}, "system": {"ch": "學士班", "en": "Undergraduate Programme"}, "language": {"ch": "英語", "en": "English"}, "card": {"ch": "部份使用", "en": "Optional"}, "assigned": 37, "selected": 0, "remark": {"ch": "", "en": ""}, "goal": {"ch": "In this course, students will: 1) articulate the ways in which fictional narratives both reflect and comment on the cultures that produces them, especially regarding the power dynamics inherent in the social constructions of gender, race, ethnicity, and sexuality; 2) gain an understanding of how literature, music, cinema, comics, fashion, television, toys and performance contribute very distinct elements to the construction of a multimodal narrative; 3) identify the complex relationship that exists between the production and consumption of media and literary texts.", "en": "In this course, students will: 1) articulate the ways in which fictional narratives both reflect and comment on the cultures that produces them, especially regarding the power dynamics inherent in the social constructions of gender, race, ethnicity, and sexuality; 2) gain an understanding of how literature, music, cinema, comics, fashion, television, toys and performance contribute very distinct elements to the construction of a multimodal narrative; 3) identify the complex relationship that exists between the production and consumption of media and literary texts."}, "outline": {"ch": "This course is an examination of the Star Wars phenomenon, as a transmedia narrative, as a cultural reflection of our world, as an object of spectacle and consumerism, and as a space of highly creative fan communities. Drawing from cultural studies, screen studies and the new discipline of participatory culture studies, the course also critically explores how Star Wars articulates social discrimination and xenophobia, issues of gender and sexuality, and notions of imperialism and colonialism. The course covers films and comics, television and fiction, even cosplay and fan art/film.", "en": "This course is an examination of the Star Wars phenomenon, as a transmedia narrative, as a cultural reflection of our world, as an object of spectacle and consumerism, and as a space of highly creative fan communities. Drawing from cultural studies, screen studies and the new discipline of participatory culture studies, the course also critically explores how Star Wars articulates social discrimination and xenophobia, issues of gender and sexuality, and notions of imperialism and colonialism. The course covers films and comics, television and fiction, even cosplay and fan art/film."}, "textbook": {"ch": "Carmelo Esterrich. Star Wars Multiverse. Rutgers University Press, 2021. The course has many additional readings and viewings. All additional material will be provided by your instructor.", "en": "Carmelo Esterrich. Star Wars Multiverse. Rutgers University Press, 2021. The course has many additional readings and viewings. All additional material will be provided by your instructor."}, "selfCompiledRate": {"ch": "0", "en": "0"}, "instructMethod": {"ch": "講授\n研討", "en": ["Lecture", "Seminar"]}, "gradMethod": {"ch": "Viewing/Reading Responses 30％, Short Essays/Projects 30％, Participation 15％, Final Assessment 25％", "en": "Viewing/Reading Responses 30％, Short Essays/Projects 30％, Participation 15％, Final Assessment 25％"}, "officeHour": {"ch": "二5三56", "en": "Tue. 13:00-14:00, Wed. 13:00-15:00"}, "teachWeeks": {"ch": "16+2", "en": "16+2"}, "flexDiscription": {"ch": "Individual meetings for FINAL ASSESSMENT", "en": "Individual meetings for FINAL ASSESSMENT"}, "domain": {"ch": "文化研究", "en": "文化研究"}, "map": {"ch": [{"competencies": "英文閱讀解析與寫作論述", "rating": "(4)高", "assesments": ["作業練習", "出席/課堂表現", "其他"]}, {"competencies": "英語溝通與文化跨越", "rating": "(4)高", "assesments": ["出席/課堂表現"]}, {"competencies": "審美欣賞與多元創意", "rating": "(4)高", "assesments": ["作業練習", "出席/課堂表現"]}, {"competencies": "人文思維與社會關懷", "rating": "(4)高", "assesments": ["作業練習", "出席/課堂表現"]}, {"competencies": "組織能力與人際合作", "rating": "(3)普通", "assesments": ["作業練習"]}], "en": [{"competencies": "English critical reading and analytical writing", "rating": "(4)High", "assesments": ["Assignments", "Attendance/Performance", "Others"]}, {"competencies": "English oral communication and cultural crossing", "rating": "(4)High", "assesments": ["Attendance/Performance"]}, {"competencies": "aesthetic appreciation and creative diversity", "rating": "(4)High", "assesments": ["Assignments", "Attendance/Performance"]}, {"competencies": "humanities visions and social intervention", "rating": "(4)High", "assesments": ["Assignments", "Attendance/Performance"]}, {"competencies": "organizational ability and team work", "rating": "(3)Medium", "assesments": ["Assignments"]}]}, "assignCriteria": {"ch": ["系所:限英美語文學系。年級:限三年級、四年級。", "系所:限英美語文學系。", "系所:限雙主修-英美語文學系。"], "en": ["Department:Department of English only.Year:Third Year、Fourth Year only.", "Department:Department of English only.", "Department:Double Major-Department of English only."]}, "preselecStu": 0, "stuGender": {"male": 0, "Female": 0}, "stuGrade": {"doctor": {}, "master": {}, "bachelor": {}}, "stus": [{"serial": "1", "stunum": "11*******", "department": "英美語文學系", "grade": "4", "class": "*", "priority": "1", "isRequired": false, "isPreselected": false, "isManuallySelected": false, "isCodeSelected": false}, {"serial": "2", "stunum": "11*******", "department": "英美語文學系", "grade": "4", "class": "*", "priority": "1", "isRequired": false, "isPreselected": false, "isManuallySelected": false, "isCodeSelected": false}, {"serial":